            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "textStyle",
                "attrs": {
                  "color": ""
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Disadvantages of Semi-Supervised Learning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "textStyle",
                "attrs": {
                  "color": ""
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "The most basic disadvantage of any "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/machine-learning/supervised-machine-learning/",
                  "target": "_blank",
                  "rel": "noopener",
                  "class": "text-muted-foreground underline underline-offset-[3px] hover:text-primary transition-colors cursor-pointer"
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "bold"
              },
              {
                "type": "underline"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Supervised Learning"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "textStyle",
                "attrs": {
                  "color": ""
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": " algorithm is that the dataset has to be hand-labeled either by a Machine Learning Engineer or a Data Scientist. This is a very "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ],
            "text": "costly process"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "textStyle",
                "attrs": {
                  "color": ""
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": ", especially when dealing with large volumes of data. The most basic disadvantage of any "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/machine-learning/supervised-unsupervised-learning/",
                  "target": "_blank",
                  "rel": "noopener",
                  "class": "text-muted-foreground underline underline-offset-[3px] hover:text-primary transition-colors cursor-pointer"
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "bold"
              },
              {
                "type": "underline"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Unsupervised Learning"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "textStyle",
                "attrs": {
                  "color": ""
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": " is that its "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "application spectrum is limited"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "textStyle",
                "attrs": {
                  "color": ""
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": ". "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "textStyle",
                "attrs": {
                  "color": ""
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "To counter these disadvantages, the concept of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Semi-Supervised Learning"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "textStyle",
                "attrs": {
                  "color": ""
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": " was introduced. In this type of learning, the algorithm is trained upon a combination of labeled and unlabelled data. Typically, this combination will contain a very small amount of labeled data and a very large amount of unlabelled data. The basic procedure involved is that first, the programmer will cluster similar data using an unsupervised learning algorithm and then use the existing labeled data to label the rest of the unlabelled data. The typical use cases of such type of algorithm have a common property among them - The acquisition of unlabelled data is relatively cheap while labeling the said data is very expensive. "
          }
        ]
      }
